-- Kim Jong Il Shows Willingness to Join Proposed Nuclear Talks, Yonhap Says
-- B y   B o m i   L i m
-- 2010-12-12T22:00:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-12/kim-jong-il-shows-willingness-to-join-six-party-nuclear-talks-yonhap-says.html
North Korean leader  Kim Jong Il  has
shown willingness to join “emergency” six-party talks China
has proposed, Yonhap News reported, citing South Korean
diplomats it didn’t identify. Kim expressed the willingness
during his meeting with Chinese State Councilor  Dai Bingguo  last
week, the Korean-language report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bomi Lim in Seoul at 
 blim30@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
